=============
GOUWRADIO-SMS
=============

DESCRIPTION
===========
Mobile frontend for the gouwradio SMS system.

TECHNOLOGY USED
===============
The SMS messages received via FrontlineSMS are logged into a local Mysql database.
Using the Zend Framework and Doctrine, these messages are displayed on a website.
To support mobile clients, we use the jQuery Mobile framework.

SETUP
=====
1. Within Fronline SMS, change the database configuration to
		mysql.database.xml
		with server.name : localhost
		server.port : 3306
		database.name : yourdbname
		username : yourusername
		password : youwpassword
   Clicking save will create a new database. Make sure the given user has sufficient rights to create a new database
2. Add extra columns to the message table
   Execute this queries:
   alter table message add column 'gouwradioDeleted' int(2) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0';
   alter table message add column 'gouwradioType' varchar(25) DEFAULT NULL;
   alter table message add column 'gouwradioNew' int(2) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1';
   alter table message add column 'gouwradioRead' int(2) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0';